#: wasted_sun/templates/day.html:103
msgid "This raises energy prices for everyone"
msgstr ""

#: wasted_sun/templates/day.html:105
msgid ""
"\n"
"    On sunny hours the Spanish peninsula often produces more solar than "
"the local grid can absorb. That energy\n"
"    goes unused while other sources (less green, more expensive ones) "
"remain in the mix. Consumers end up paying for flexibility and system\n"
"    constraints twice over. This is measurable, costly, and largely "
"avoidable with better infrastructure\n"
"    and market design.\n"
"    "
msgstr ""

#: wasted_sun/templates/day.html:113
msgid ""
"\n"
"    <strong>What would help?</strong> Stronger grids, storage (that's "
"batteries!) and price signals that reward\n"
"    using clean power when it is abundant. That reduces waste, eases "
"bills, and puts scarce clean\n"
"    generation to work.\n"
"    "
msgstr ""

#: wasted_sun/templates/day.html:122
msgid "Put in perspective"
msgstr ""

#: wasted_sun/templates/day.html:124
#, python-format
msgid ""
"\n"
"    Today's unused solar total is in the ballpark of the daily "
"electricity of about\n"
"    <strong>%(homes)s</strong> typical homes, using an illustrative "
"%(kwh)s kWh per home per day\n"
"    for scale (not a census count - see methodology).\n"
"    "
msgstr ""

#: wasted_sun/templates/day.html:133
msgid "Methodology"
msgstr ""

#: wasted_sun/templates/day.html:135
msgid ""
"\n"
"    Quarter-hourly unused solar (MWh) is derived from Red Eléctrica de "
"España (REE) data, processed in\n"
"    a separate pipeline and stored in this project's database: each row "
"is keyed by date with\n"
"    15-minute buckets of unused energy. Multiple rows for the same day "
"are summed\n"
"    bucket-wise before display.\n"
"    "
msgstr ""

#: wasted_sun/templates/day.html:143
msgid ""
"\n"
"    The chart aggregates those quarter-hours into 24 hourly bars. Any "
"slots\n"
"    beyond the first 96 are folded into the last hour of the day. Day "
"totals are the sum of all\n"
"    quarter-hour values. “So far this year” uses the sum of MWh across "
"rows from 1st January through the\n"
"    selected date. The average “per hour” figure is the mean of the 24 "
"hourly bars (equivalently the\n"
"    day total divided by 24).\n"
"    "
msgstr ""

#: wasted_sun/templates/day.html:152
msgid ""
"\n"
"    Euro amounts appear as a simple illustrative rate for energy, not a "
"market settlement: but they make clear that unused MWh are not "
"economically neutral.\n"
"    "
msgstr ""

#: wasted_sun/templates/day.html:156
msgid "Household analogy"
msgstr ""

#: wasted_sun/templates/day.html:158
msgid ""
"\n"
"    The household comparison uses a configurable illustrative kWh/day "
"figure to give an intuitive\n"
"    scale.\n"
"    "
msgstr ""

